HEADWORD: Protactinium
<hw>Protactinium</hw>. <def>The radioactive chemical element, of atomic
number 91; Atomic symbol Pa; at. wt. of longest-lived isotope, 231
(T<subs>⟦frac12⟧</subs> = 32,500 yrs.) Also called brevium, Uranium X2
and UX2.</def>⟦br⟧
